    "description": "<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Puzzles</h2><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1125880/extras/8140bc699f5d3e5bbed66392064e30a8.poster.avif?t=1627995192\" width=800 height=224 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1125880/extras/8140bc699f5d3e5bbed66392064e30a8.webm?t=1627995192\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1125880/extras/8140bc699f5d3e5bbed66392064e30a8.mp4?t=1627995192\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span><br><br>LaserZone is a Sci-Fi, top-down puzzle game.<br>In this game, you will be playing as ‘Handel’;<br>the protagonist who finds himself trapped inside lethal puzzles, <br>and aims to escape by using his brainpower.<br><br>LaserZone uses easy-to-understand science concepts as puzzle mechanics. <br>For example,<br><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li>Rotate Prisms to <u>reflect</u> Lasers.<br></li><li>Exploit <u>velocity</u> and <u>force</u> from Moving Walks and Gravity Turrets to move objects.<br></li><li>Use Switches and EMP Gun to <u>power up and down</u> traps.  </li></ul><br>What you might have come across during science class in school, now returns as puzzles in a concise fashion.<br>This is the key feature of the LaserZone.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Actions</h2><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1125880/extras/30463449fe895b1c0b97694621287a3d.poster.avif?t=1627995192\" width=800 height=224 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1125880/extras/30463449fe895b1c0b97694621287a3d.webm?t=1627995192\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1125880/extras/30463449fe895b1c0b97694621287a3d.mp4?t=1627995192\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span><br><br>Sometimes, in LaserZone, <u>reflexes</u> are crucial for your escape.<br><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li>Bullets force-open Item Boxes for you, but sometimes can form a dangerous barrage in certain maps.<br></li><li>Gravity Towers that push or pull objects may drive you into a Minefield.<br></li><li>If you somehow survived, then robots will appear to take you down.</li></ul><br>LaserZone is indeed about solving puzzles. <br>But sometimes, you’ll need to fight and evade.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Tools and Upgrades</h2><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1125880/extras/56fab50d5edf695c2cbd5143944667ac.avif?t=1627995192\" width=600 height=168 /></span><br><br>As you continue the game, the difficulty will generally increase.<br>However, you will be given Tools and Upgrades to overcome any difficulties.<br><br>You may acquire a few equipment with luck, <br>but most upgrades will cost Resources which must be earned with effort.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Plot, Story &amp; Directing</h2><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1125880/extras/66e5f24adf416c094a1396504ce92242.avif?t=1627995192\" width=800 height=450 /></span><br><br>Handel wakes up inside his crash-landed spaceship, suffering a loss of memory.<br>He searches nearby places to recover from amnesia and find usable parts for the spaceship.<br>Shortly, he sets his foot in an enormous facility, unknowing the existence of deadly traps lurking inside.<br>Will he be able to recover his memory, and reclaim the treasure greater than his own life?<br><br>Several characters including Handel will appear in LaserZone.<br>Handel talks with them, sometimes confront them, reminds himself of what happened in the past, and moves forward to end the journey once and for all.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Art</h2><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1125880/extras/ffbb8a6c6c001c48cf39f57284bfe140.avif?t=1627995192\" width=800 height=450 /></span><br><br>LaserZone is a 2D game with a three-dimensional effect. It is built based on <u>Cycles Render</u> from Blender Cycles 3D Tool.<br><br>Thanks to Cycles Render's power, we have created a world brimming with futuristic artworks and Sci-Fi atmosphere.<br><br><br><i>* LaserZone uses free classic music as BGM, whose copyrights AND neighboring copyrights have expired.</i>",
